SIMPLE: unmake
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unmake
<hw>Un*make"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>make</ets>.]</ety> <def>To destroy the form and
qualities of; to deprive of being; to uncreate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>God does not make or <qex>unmake</qex> things to try
experiments.</q> <rj><qau>T. Burnet.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unman</ent>⟦br⟧
